menu "breadboard: bb_nv"

config BB_NV_CREDS_RTC_BACKUP
    bool "Back up wifi creds to RTC slow memory (survive NVS erase-on-corruption)"
    default y
    help
      Mirrors wifi ssid/pass/provisioned (~108 bytes) into RTC_NOINIT memory so a
      crash-induced NVS erase doesn't strand a headless board. Survives software
      reset/panic; lost on full power-off. See B1-242.

config BB_NV_FACTORY_RESET
    bool "Enable POST /api/factory-reset route (full NVS wipe + deferred reboot)"
    default n
    help
      When enabled, registers POST /api/factory-reset. A valid request body
      {"confirm":"factory-reset"} erases the entire NVS partition (all namespaces),
      invalidates the RTC creds mirror so the restore-heal path cannot resurrect
      credentials, responds 202, then reboots after ~500 ms. Disabled by default
      because factory reset is a destructive operation that should be opt-in.

endmenu
